UPON UNLOADING THE V EHICLE IN ROCHESTER, NY OUR DRIVER NOTED THAT ONE OF THE COLUMNS HAD CRACKE D AND SPILLED MERCURY INTO THE BODY OF THE TRUCK. REPRESENTATIVES OF TAYLOR INSTRUMENTS VACCUMED ALL SPILLED MERCURY FROM THE FLOOR OF THE TRUCK. IT I S ESTIMATED THAT A TOTAL OF THREE TO FOUR POUNDS OF MERCURY WAS SPILLED. KE VIN HYLTON OF TAYLOR INSTRUMENTS REPORTED THE SPILL TO THE NATIONAL RESPONS E CENTER OF THE UNITED STATES ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION AGENCY. MERCURY VAPO R MONITORS WERE IN USE THROUGHOUT THE REMAINDER OF THE DAY AND SHOWED STEAD ILY DECREASING LEVELS. THE VAN WAS RETURNED TO ATLANTA AND WAS THERE RETEST ED FOR MERCURY VAPOR LEVEL.
